item.title: VICTORY!! Jwow
item.description:
VICTORY!! Jwow
On this episode of Miss Hannah Minx's JWOW (Japanese Word of the Week), our work is "Yatta!" Yatta is the past tense of "yaru," meaning "to do." So Yatta! means, "I did it!" Yatta as an exclamation can be translated as "Victory!," "Alright!" "I did it!" Yatta can also be used in a different, non-positive sense, but is usually positive as a victorious exclamation! v(^.^)v Leave a video response of when you say Yatta!!
